      "rationale": "The SST k-ω turbulence model was selected based on a turbulence model sensitivity study comparing k-ε, SST k-ω, and RSM across three operating points; SST k-ω minimized NIH prediction error (MAE 18.4% vs. 24.1% for k-ε). The Giersiepen–Wurzinger hemolysis model was selected per FDA benchmark guidance. Model form uncertainty is quantified via Bayesian model averaging over three hemolysis model variants; 90% credible interval reported. Model form assessment meets MRL-5.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
