      "rationale": "All model inputs characterized with probability distributions: blood viscosity (normal, μ=0.0035 Pa·s, σ=0.0003), density (normal, μ=1060 kg/m³, σ=10), power-law exponent α (uniform, 0.62–0.78), power-law coefficient C (log-normal, μ=3.62×10⁻⁵, σ=20%). Distributions sourced from peer-reviewed literature and manufacturer data sheets. Monte Carlo propagation with 4096 samples yields 90% prediction interval on NIH. Input uncertainty dominates total output uncertainty at MRL-5.",
