  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou2/decision",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/org/morrison-vv40-team/lead-assessor",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors have been assessed at MRL-5. Achieved levels meet or exceed required levels for all factors: five factors achieved Gradation 5 (SQA, code verification, discretization error, solver error, model form, model inputs) and seven factors achieved Gradation 4 against a Gradation 4 requirement (test conditions, output comparison, QoI relevance, validation relevance, use error, test samples, input equivalency). No factor exhibits a shortfall. The global sensitivity analysis identifies the Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law exponent as the dominant uncertainty driver (S1=0.61); this has been addressed through Bayesian model averaging and a fully characterized input distribution. Monte Carlo UQ with 4096 samples provides 90% prediction intervals that bracket all experimental observations. The validation metric E < 1.0 at all five operating points confirms the model is fit for purpose within the defined COU. The operating envelope and applicability constraints are concretely bounded and all simulation operating points lie strictly within the validated space. The provenance chain from raw experimental data through validation activities to this assessment record is complete and traceable. On the basis of the complete structured evidence, the credibility assessment team accepts the CFD hemolysis model for predicting absolute NIH values for the Class III VAD COU.",
